summary:
**Coordination and Outreach**

* Reiterates the need for enhanced cooperation among the Committee, CTC, and the Committee established pursuant to resolution 1540 (2004) (para. 35)
* Encourages the Monitoring Team and UN Office on Drugs and Crime to continue joint activities to assist Member States (para. 36)
* Requests the Committee to consider visits to selected countries to enhance implementation of measures (para. 37)

**Reporting and Monitoring**

* Requests the Committee to report orally to the Council at least every 180 days on its work and the Monitoring Team (para. 38)
* Decides to extend the mandate of the Monitoring Team for 18 months (para. 39)

**Reviews and Next Steps**

* Decides to review the measures described in paragraph 1 with a view to their possible further strengthening in 18 months, or sooner if necessary (para. 40)
* Decides to remain actively seized of the matter (para. 41)
The Monitoring Team, operating under the direction of the Committee established pursuant to resolution 1267 (1999), shall have the following responsibilities:

(a) Submit two comprehensive reports to the Committee by 28 February 2009 and 31 July 2009 on implementation of measures by States;

(b) Analyse reports and information submitted by Member States;

(c) Assist the Committee in following-up on requests to Member States for information;

(d) Submit a program of work to the Committee for review and approval;

(e) Work closely with CTED and the 1540 Committee's group of experts;

(f) Participate in and support activities under the UN Global Counter-Terrorism Strategy;

(g) Assist the Committee in analyzing non-compliance;

(h) Present recommendations to assist Member States with implementation;

(i) Assist in compiling publicly releasable information;

(j) Consult with Member States before travel;

(k) Encourage Member States to submit names for the Consolidated List;

(l) Present additional identifying information to update the Consolidated List;

(m) Study and report on the changing nature of the Al-Qaida and Taliban threat;

(n) Collate, assess, monitor and report on implementation of measures;

(o) Consult with Member States and organizations;

(p) Consult with intelligence and security services;

(q) Consult with private sector representatives;

(r) Work with international and regional organizations;

(s) Work with INTERPOL for listed individuals' photographs;

(t) Assist other subsidiary bodies with INTERPOL cooperation;
